  <static seed="116" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberAdditionWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>To pave the road on Ellis Street, the crew used <m>3{{\frac{7}{10}}}</m> tons of cement on the first day, and used <m>4{{\frac{1}{2}}}</m> tons on the second day. How many tons of cement were used in all?</p>
<p><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> tons of cement were used in all.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>8{\textstyle\frac{1}{5}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This problem is obviously an addition problem.</p>
<p>To add mixed number, we break each mixed number into an integer and a fraction, and then add up integers and fractions separately.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
3{{\frac{7}{10}}} + 4{{\frac{1}{2}}} 
      \amp = 3 + {{\frac{7}{10}}} + 4 + {{\frac{1}{2}}} \\
      \amp = 3 + 4 + {{\frac{7}{10}}} + {{\frac{1}{2}}} \\
      \amp = 7 + \frac{7}{10} + \frac{1 \cdot 5}{2 \cdot 5} \\
      \amp = 7 + \frac{7}{10} + \frac{5}{10} \\
      \amp = 7 + \frac{12}{10} \\
      \amp = 7 + \frac{6}{5} \\
      \amp = 7 + {1{\textstyle\frac{1}{5}}} \\
      \amp = {8{\textstyle\frac{1}{5}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p><m>{8{\textstyle\frac{1}{5}}}</m> tons of cement were used in all.</p>
</solution>
